      <h2>About Cars</h2>
      <p>
        Cars are more than just a mode of transport—they represent
        <b>freedom, style, and innovation</b>. From the invention of the first
        motor vehicle in the late 19th century to today's high-performance
        machines, cars have continued to
        <b>evolve with technology, speed, and design</b>.
      </p>
      <h3>Types of Cars</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>Vintage Cars</b> - Classic beauties from the past, prized by
          collectors.
        </li>
        <li><b>Sports Cars</b> - Built for speed, style, and performance.</li>
        <li>
          <b>SUVs</b> - Spacious, powerful, and perfect for families or
          adventures.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Luxury Cars</b> - Premium comfort, cutting-edge features, and
          elegance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Electric Cars (EVs)</b> - Eco-friendly vehicles powered by
          electricity.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Fun Car Facts</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>The <b>first car</b> was invented by <b>Karl Benz in 1886</b>.</li>
        <li>
          The <b>world's fastest car</b> (as of 2025) can reach speeds of over
          <b>500 km/h</b>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Vintage Mustangs and Camaros</b> are among the most popular classic
          muscle cars.
        </li>
        <li>
          Modern cars come with <b>AI, autopilot, and electric drivetrains</b>.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

