    <div class="car-info">
      <h2>Modified Cars</h2>
      <p>
        Modified cars are vehicles that have been customized to improve their
        <span class="highlight">performance, style, or both</span>. Enthusiasts
        upgrade engines, change body designs, install advanced exhaust systems,
        or add unique paint jobs to create a car that reflects their
        <b>individual personality and taste</b>.
      </p>

      <h3>Types of Car Modifications</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>Performance Mods</b> - Engine tuning, turbochargers, and exhaust
          systems to increase speed and power.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Visual Mods</b> - Custom paint, vinyl wraps, spoilers, body kits,
          and rims for a unique look.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Interior Mods</b> - Upgraded seats, steering wheels, audio systems,
          and lighting.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Suspension Mods</b> - Lowered suspension or hydraulic setups for
          better handling or style.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Technology Mods</b> - Adding advanced sound systems, digital
          displays, or smart gadgets.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Why People Modify Cars?</h3>
      <p>
        Car modification is not just about power—it's about
        <span class="highlight">creativity and identity</span>. Many owners
        modify cars to stand out, achieve better performance, or simply follow
        their passion for automotive art. In car culture, modified cars are
        often seen as <b>expressions of freedom</b>.
      </p>

      <h3>Popular Modified Car Trends</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>JDM (Japanese Domestic Market)</b> - Famous for cars like the
          Nissan Skyline, Toyota Supra, and Honda Civic.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Muscle Car Mods</b> - Classic Mustangs, Camaros, and Challengers
          with massive engines and bold looks.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Euro Mods</b> - German cars like BMW, Audi, and Volkswagen with
          sleek tuning and premium finishes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Off-Road Mods</b> - Jeeps, Land Cruisers, and SUVs with big tires,
          lift kits, and rugged gear.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>The Future of Modified Cars</h3>
      <p>
        With the rise of <span class="highlight">electric vehicles (EVs)</span>,
        car modification is entering a new era. EV owners are now customizing
        battery packs, digital dashboards, and futuristic body kits. The culture
        of modified cars will continue to evolve, blending
        <b>classic car passion with modern technology</b>.
      </p>
    </div>
